  "prompt": "What are the some good movies to watch?",
  "response": "There are many great movies across various genres that you might enjoy. Here are some recommendations:\n\n### Drama\n1. **Shawshank Redemption (1994)** - A story of hope and friendship inside a maximum-security prison.\n2. **The Godfather (1972)** - A classic crime film detailing the mafia dynasty.\n3. **Forrest Gump (1994)** - A heartwarming tale of an unlikely hero witnessing important moments in American history.\n\n### Action\n1. **Mad Max: Fury Road (2015)** - A post-apocalyptic chase across the wasteland.\n2. **Die Hard (1988)** - A gripping action film centered around a hostage situation.\n3. **John Wick (2014)** - A stylish and intense martial arts action saga.\n\n### Comedy\n1. **Groundhog Day (1993)** - A man continuously relives the same day in this witty time-loop movie.\n2. **Superbad (2007)** - A high school comedy focusing on friendship and ridiculous antics.\n3. **Monty Python and the Holy Grail (1975)** - An absurd and hilarious take on the King Arthur legend.\n\n### Sci-Fi & Fantasy\n1. **Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope (1977)** - The beginning of the epic space saga.\n2. **Blade Runner (1982)** - A futuristic detective story exploring the nature of humanity.\n3. **The Matrix (1999)** - A mind-bending film about reality and artificial intelligence.\n\n### Thriller\n1. **Inception (2010)** - A cerebral thriller where dreams are manipulated.\n2. **Se7en (1995)** - A dark, immersive investigation into a series of gruesome murders.\n3. **Gone Girl (2014)** - A twisting tale of a missing wife and media frenzy.\n\n### Horror\n1. **The Shining (1980)** - A haunting story of isolation and madness in a remote hotel.\n2. **Get Out (2017)** - A psychological horror movie with strong social themes.\n3. **A Quiet Place (2018)** - A thrilling horror film reliant on suspense and silence.\n\n### Animation\n1. **Toy Story (1995)** - A beloved, innovative tale about the secret life of toys.\n2. **Spirited Away (2001)** - A magical journey in a fantastical world.\n3. **Coco (2017)** - A touching story about family and Mexican folklore.\n\n### Recent Releases (as of 2023)\n1. **Everything Everywhere All at Once (2022)** - A genre-bending adventure of multiverses.\n2. **Dune (2021)** - A breathtaking adaptation of the classic sci-fi novel.\n3. **Top Gun: Maverick (2022)** - A high-flying sequel to the iconic 1986 action film.\n\nThese are just a few examples, and taste in movies can vary greatly. Consider what genres you enjoy most and try finding films within those categories.",
